				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Its all about the wall....<a name="72973"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 7 05 10:49 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In EQI I felt I was up against the wall. Huge amounts of effort for a small gain that I may not be able to notice.
<br />

<br />
In EQII, the gains come often, realitively easily at my level and you see the benefit. Rumors are this game is designed for a couple hundred level.
<br />

<br />
I don't have to deal with twinks.
<br />

<br />
So far, I'm not walled out of content by huge guild/raid required timesinks.
<br />

<br />
I'll admit that the social side of adventuring isn't what it was in EQI, but if you are into that, tradeskill...those folks tend to be really friendly.
<br />

<br />
There are a lot of the same problems that existed in EQI (inept players, jerks, timesinks, fewer but still annoying bugs, etc, etc). Nevertheless, its still novel and different.
<br />

<br />

<br />
There you got a serious answer where you probably weren't looking for one.
<br />

<br />
I went back to my EQI bard while my account was still active. After an hour of twisting I asked myself, &quot;Why the he77 did I ever do this????&quot; EQII really benefits the play style that has evolved for me. They even re-geared the game more to it.
<br />

<br />
EQI was fun, but this is funner...at least for me at this point.
<br />

<br />

<br />
PS. I spent some time exploring the Enchanted Lands last night..in it is Rivervale gone outlaw. I am gonna get to gut and hang haflings out to dry. IT JUST DOESN'T GET ANY BETTER THAN THAT! ..........ummm ummm hafling!
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
