personally I've been playing both EQ1 and EQ2..   I had canceled my eq1 account.. but since its on a 6 month term.. I'm stuck with it till  april.. 
<br />

<br />
well so I thought..  Lately after playing EQ2 for a bit.. I just find that I'm playing EQ1 more often than EQ2.    I always pride myself at being a good bard in EQ1,  where I know I can make or break an encounter..   
<br />

<br />
WIth EQ2, I can't say that..  maybe I've been unlucky with groups...  or its just that maybe I don't understand the class I'm playing..  (playing troubador level 22)   or it could be I'm such a low level that I'm not having the fun that i have with my bard in EQ1.. 
<br />

<br />
Anyways.. different game mechanic's   EQ2 is fun for certain things (heck I'm even doing tradeskilling in eq2, never did it in eq1) 
<br />

<br />
Anyways, currently I'm still playing EQ1,  and I'm finding that I'll probably restart my subscription again, come April..    haven't decided about Eq2 yet..  I'm having fun in EQ2.. but to me, it seems to lack something..  I'm not entirely sure what tho.  Maybe if I get to higher level I'll see..
