				<td colspan="2"><span>I do not like the combat mechanics in EQ2 even 1/2 as much as in EQ1, but EQ2 is way more fun for me. Personally the grind in EQ does me in, and i need to do something to break up the monotony...problem is I trully do not like tradeskills on EQ1. I didnt get very high. only 150 jewelery, 200+ fletching but i had 0 fun getting to those points. none. I primarily tradeskill in EQ2, and love the heck out of it. Then when I get tired, I go out and adventure, harvest....oooh harvest rares! Harvesting on EQ1?  :(....And oh what an inventory of trash I had.  Even as a 10-19 outfitter I can make some very useful things...and keep getting better(25 weaponsmith so far). @ TS level 15 I made my entire outfit, and it was really good. Low skilled tradeskiller on EQ 1 sports some REAL trash...even mid levels I wasnt making anything very useful. Yes, for me, EQ1 barding is so much more fun....but so much more to do on EQ2, I forget how to fight @ times. Oh yes and no twinks, or Power leveling. Community seems just as good too. If they could only merge the 2 together. I hate the combat circling....and pulling is no fun either. That is my favorite part of EQ 1... especially LDoN pulling:). I didnt play EQ1 entirely too long, so maybe i missed something with the TS, but should have done more to keep my attention in the beginning. EQ2 keeps my attention the whole way. just IMO </span></td>
